# Component Development Rules - NextFab

## Struktura Komponentów
```typescript
// Template dla komponenta aplikacyjnego
interface ComponentProps {
  // Props definition
}

export const Component = ({ ...props }: ComponentProps) => {
  // Component logic
  
  return (
    // JSX with proper accessibility
  );
};

Component.displayName = 'Component';
```

## Design System Integration
- Używaj tokenów z Chakra UI v3
- Komponenty prymitywne w src/components/ui/
- Komponenty aplikacyjne z proper naming

## Accessibility (a11y)
- Proper ARIA labels
- Keyboard navigation support
- Screen reader compatibility
- Color contrast compliance

## Performance Optimization
- React.memo dla expensive components
- useMemo/useCallback gdzie appropriate
- Lazy loading dla heavy components

## Props Pattern
```typescript
// Base props pattern
interface BaseProps {
  className?: string;
  children?: React.ReactNode;
  'data-testid'?: string;
}

interface SpecificProps extends BaseProps {
  // Specific component props
}
```

## Error Boundaries
```typescript
// Component-level error handling
const ComponentWithErrorBoundary = () => (
  <ErrorBoundary fallback={<ComponentFallback />}>
    <Component />
  </ErrorBoundary>
